habitat: 10-acre island located in the mouth of the Kennebec River in Georgetown; Sagadahoc County. The island includes a variety of habitats including sandy beach; beach grass meadow; poison ivy/raspberry shrubland; fescue meadows and steep rocky sea cliffs.
164 acres of predominantly mixed hemlock-hardwood; with a mixed history of cutting and disturbance.
